[1] Case update
- Thu 11 Jul 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=0e6f57b1d3

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 10 Jul 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 2437, of which 2343 are confirmed and 94 are probable. In total, there were 1646 deaths (1552 confirmed and 94 probable) and 683 people healed.
- 358 suspected cases under investigation;
- 9 new confirmed cases, including 6 in Beni, 1 in Mambasa, 1 in Kalunguta and 1 in Katwa;
- 5 new confirmed case deaths: 5 community deaths -- 2 in Beni, 1 in Oicha, 1 in Mambasa and 1 in Kalunguta; data on deaths of confirmed cases managed by Ebola treatment centers (ETCs) are not available this [Wed 10 Jul 2019].

News
Epidemiological surveillance
-------------------------
- New health area affected: Mambasa (Ituri). The 1st case is an 8-year-old boy residing in Mambasa who had been to Beni with his mother. His mother, confirmed to have Ebola, died in Beni on 19 Jun 2019, but she was not buried in a dignified and secure manner. After developing the disease, the boy returned to Mambasa with his uncle. He died at the Mambasa Reference General Hospital.

Figures of the response
----------------------
- 156 851 vaccinated persons
- 73 466 784 people under control [includes same individual coming and going through checkpoints]
-- 80 entry points (PoE) and operational health checkpoints (PoC)
- 131 contaminated health workers
-- 3 health workers, including 2 vaccinated, are among the new confirmed cases (1 in Beni, 1 in Kalunguta and 1 in Katwa). The unvaccinated Kalunguta health worker died in a community health center.
-- The cumulative number of confirmed / probable cases among health workers is 131 (5% of all confirmed / probable cases), including 41 deaths.

