3. This is how #Ebola spreads: An 8 yo boy whose mother died from Ebola in Beni was taken to his uncle in Mambasa. The boy developed Ebola & died from the infection. Mambasa hadn't previously had cases. Sigh (for the child & for the spread.)]

- Fri 12 Jul 2019.
[WHO dashboard, edited]
https://who.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/e70c3804f6044652bc37cce7d8fcef6c

The MoH/WHO AFRO Ebola DRC KIVU 2018 Dashboard reports 11 new cases on 11 Jul [2019], making a total so far this week of 43, 246 in the past 21 days, and 2461 since the outbreak began last August [2018]. Out of 17 800 contacts, 1800 are going untraced.

